Pinyin Chart

Above you’ll find a complete chart with all the different pinyin combinations. Click on any combination to see all the tones and for real (non-computerized) audio for every sound.

Pronounce Each Sound?

While other websites include a lengthy explanation about how to say each sound we believe in the practical method. Use the chart above to listen to each sound. You’ll soon find that there are patterns which are reasonably easy to follow, and that generally speaking, each “consonant” and each “vowel combination” for the most part follow set rules. There are a few exceptions though so listen carefully!

Once you think you’re getting the hang of it, of if you just want to throw yourself in the deep end, you can test yourself with real audio using our Tones Practice tool! (FREE – but you need to create an account)
